
[1]wail

   WAIL, v.t. To lament; to moan; to bewail.

   Or if no more her absent lord she wails--

               WAIL, v.i. To weep; to express sorrow audibly.

   Therefore I will wail and howl. Micah 1.

                 WAIL, n. Loud weeping; violent lamentation.
